import json
import sys
import csv

def flatten_participants(participants, primary_member_reference):
    flat_data = []
    for participant in participants:
        for role in participant['role']:
            if 'coding' in role:
                for code_info in role['coding']:
                    entry = {
                        'member_reference': primary_member_reference,  # Consistent member reference for all
                        'member_display': participant['member'].get('display', ''),
                        'role_system': code_info['system'],
                        'role_code': code_info['code'],
                        'role_display': code_info['display']
                    }
                    flat_data.append(entry)
    return flat_data

def json_to_csv(filename):
    # Read from standard input
    data = json.load(sys.stdin)

    # Extract the primary member_reference from the subject reference of the care team
    primary_member_reference = data['resource']['subject']['reference']

    base_info = {
        'fullUrl': data['fullUrl'],
        'resourceType': data['resource']['resourceType'],
        'careTeam_id': data['resource']['id'],
        'status': data['resource']['status'],
        'subject_reference': primary_member_reference,  # Use the primary reference for all
        'encounter_reference': data['resource']['encounter']['reference'],
        'period_start': data['resource']['period']['start'],
        'managingOrganization_display': data['resource']['managingOrganization'][0]['display'],
        'filename': filename
    }

    # Flatten the participant data
    participants = flatten_participants(data['resource']['participant'], primary_member_reference)

    # Append base info to each participant for full schema compliance
    for participant in participants:
        participant.update(base_info)

    # Write to CSV
    fieldnames = participants[0].keys() if participants else []
    writer = csv.DictWriter(sys.stdout, fieldnames=fieldnames, quoting=csv.QUOTE_ALL)
    writer.writeheader()
    for participant in participants:
        writer.writerow(participant)

if __name__ == '__main__':
    if len(sys.argv) > 1:
        filename = sys.argv[1]  # Get filename from the command line argument
        json_to_csv(filename)
    else:
        print("Error: No filename provided.")

import json
import sys
import csv

# Define the function to extract nested values safely
def get_nested(data, *args, default=None):
    for arg in args:
        try:
            data = data[arg]
        except (IndexError, KeyError, TypeError):
            return default
    return data

# Define the function to process the ExplanationOfBenefit
def process_benefit(json_data, filename):
    # Flatten the data into a list of dictionaries for each item
    items = []
    
    # Common identifiers for mapping
    full_url = json_data['fullUrl']
    subject_reference = get_nested(json_data, 'resource', 'patient', 'reference', default='unknown')

    # Process each item
    for item in get_nested(json_data, 'resource', 'item', default=[]):
        encounter_references = [get_nested(enc, 'reference', default='unknown') for enc in item.get('encounter', [])]

        item_details = {
            'fullUrl': full_url,
            'subject_reference': subject_reference,
            'encounter_reference': "; ".join(encounter_references),
            'filename': filename,  # Include the filename in each item
            'sequence': get_nested(item, 'sequence', default=''),
            'productServiceCode': get_nested(item, 'productOrService', 'coding', 0, 'code', default=''),
            'productServiceDisplay': get_nested(item, 'productOrService', 'coding', 0, 'display', default=''),
            'servicedStart': get_nested(item, 'servicedPeriod', 'start', default=''),
            'servicedEnd': get_nested(item, 'servicedPeriod', 'end', default=''),
            'locationDisplay': get_nested(item, 'locationCodeableConcept', 'coding', 0, 'display', default=''),
            'netValue': get_nested(item, 'net', 'value', default=''),
            'netCurrency': get_nested(item, 'net', 'currency', default=''),
        }
        items.append(item_details)

    # Output as CSV with all fields quoted
    fieldnames = items[0].keys() if items else []
    writer = csv.DictWriter(sys.stdout, fieldnames=fieldnames, quoting=csv.QUOTE_ALL)
    writer.writeheader()
    for item in items:
        writer.writerow(item)

if __name__ == "__main__":
    if len(sys.argv) > 1:
        filename = sys.argv[1]  # Get filename from the command line argument
        json_data = json.load(sys.stdin)
        process_benefit(json_data, filename)
    else:
        print("Error: No filename provided.")

import json
import sys
import csv

def flatten_claim_items(items, filename):
    """Flatten the claim item data into a list of dictionaries."""
    flat_items = []
    for item in items:
        entry = {
            'item_sequence': item.get('sequence', ''),
            'product_service_code': item['productOrService']['coding'][0].get('code', ''),
            'product_service_display': item['productOrService']['coding'][0].get('display', ''),
            'product_service_text': item['productOrService'].get('text', ''),
            'net_value': item.get('net', {}).get('value', ''),
            'net_currency': item.get('net', {}).get('currency', ''),
            'encounter_reference': item.get('encounter', [{}])[0].get('reference', ''),
            'diagnosis_sequence': item.get('diagnosisSequence', [])[0] if item.get('diagnosisSequence', []) else '',
            'filename': filename  # Include the filename in each item
        }
        flat_items.append(entry)
    return flat_items

def process_claims(filename):
    # Read JSON data from standard input
    data = json.load(sys.stdin)

    # Extract base claim info
    claim_info = {
        'fullUrl': data['fullUrl'],
        'claim_id': data['resource']['id'],
        'status': data['resource']['status'],
        'claim_type': data['resource']['type']['coding'][0]['code'],
        'use': data['resource']['use'],
        'patient_reference': data['resource']['patient']['reference'],
        'patient_display': data['resource']['patient']['display'],
        'provider_reference': data['resource']['provider']['reference'],
        'provider_display': data['resource']['provider']['display'],
        'billable_period_start': data['resource']['billablePeriod']['start'],
        'billable_period_end': data['resource']['billablePeriod']['end'],
        'created': data['resource']['created'],
        'total_value': data['resource']['total']['value'],
        'total_currency': data['resource']['total']['currency'],
        'filename': filename  # Add filename to the base claim info
    }

    # Flatten the claim items data
    items = flatten_claim_items(data['resource']['item'], filename)

    # Add claim base info to each row in items list
    for item in items:
        item.update(claim_info)

    # Write items to CSV, ensuring all fields are properly escaped and quoted
    if items:
        fieldnames = items[0].keys()
        writer = csv.DictWriter(sys.stdout, fieldnames=fieldnames, quoting=csv.QUOTE_ALL)
        writer.writeheader()
        for item in items:
            writer.writerow(item)
    else:
        print("No data to process.")

if __name__ == '__main__':
    if len(sys.argv) > 1:
        filename = sys.argv[1]  # Get filename from the command line argument
        process_claims(filename)
    else:
        print("Error: No filename provided.")

import json
import sys
import csv

def process_condition(filename):
    # Read JSON data from standard input
    data = json.load(sys.stdin)

    # Extract base condition info
    condition_info = {
        'fullUrl': data['fullUrl'],
        'condition_id': data['resource']['id'],
        'clinical_status': data['resource']['clinicalStatus']['coding'][0]['code'],
        'verification_status': data['resource']['verificationStatus']['coding'][0]['code'],
        'condition_category': data['resource']['category'][0]['coding'][0]['display'],
        'condition_code': data['resource']['code']['coding'][0]['code'],
        'condition_display': data['resource']['code']['coding'][0]['display'],
        'condition_text': data['resource']['code'].get('text', ''),
        'subject_reference': data['resource']['subject']['reference'],
        'encounter_reference': data['resource']['encounter']['reference'],
        'onsetDateTime': data['resource']['onsetDateTime'],
        'recordedDate': data['resource']['recordedDate'],
        'filename': filename  # Adding filename to the base info
    }

    # Open standard output as a CSV writer
    writer = csv.DictWriter(sys.stdout, fieldnames=condition_info.keys(), quoting=csv.QUOTE_ALL)
    writer.writeheader()
    writer.writerow(condition_info)

if __name__ == '__main__':
    if len(sys.argv) > 1:
        filename = sys.argv[1]  # Get filename from the command line argument
        process_condition(filename)
    else:
        print("Error: No filename provided.")
